public KijiDelete(EntityId entityId,
                  String family,

Creates a new KijiDelete for all versions of a family. This is not supported on map type families.

Parameters:
entityId - The entityId of the row to delete.
family - The family of the column to delete.
scope - Indication to delete all or latest version.

KijiDelete

public KijiDelete(EntityId entityId,
                  String family,
                  Long timestamp,
                  KijiDelete.KijiDeleteScope scope)
Creates a new KijiDelete for all versions of the family up to this timestamp. This is not supported on map type families.

Parameters:
entityId - The entityId of the row to delete.
family - The family of the column to delete.
timestamp - The version of the row to delete.
scope - Indication to delete upto a version or the exact version.

Parameters:
entityId - The entityId of the row to delete.
family - The family of the column to delete
qualifier - The qualifier of the column to delete
scope - The scope of delete, i.e. all versions or latest (specified by exact)

KijiDelete

public KijiDelete(EntityId entityId,
                  String family,
                  String qualifier,
                  Long timestamp,
                  KijiDelete.KijiDeleteScope scope)
Creates a new KijiDelete for a specific column within a family. The scope along with the timestamp decides whether to delete all versions up to this timestamp or only the version specified by timestamp.

Parameters:
entityId - The entityId of the row to delete.
family - The family of the column to delete.
qualifier - The qualifier of the column to delete.
timestamp - The version of the row to delete.
scope - The scope of the delete, i.e. up to or the exact version
